values: September 18, 2004. the best day of my life! DJ and I went to San Fran to see Haste The Day and met Kamy and Zach there. It was the best show! We used all of our money and had to scrape for change just to get into the show. So, with Haste The Day playing in Roseville tonight, we were both totally bummed when we realized we wouldn't have enough money to get in. Anyways, after they played Jimmy came over and talked to us, and he's going to try and get us into the show tonight! I have never been so excited ever! Wish us luck!

HEY! I just moved to Folsom over last weekend, so all ya'll need to come visit me soon! My job is a lot better now, I work every day for the next two weeks. its cool, i need the money BAD! and school is great, i love it! i miss everyone, the last time i've seen ANYONE was Jonny at school the other day! we all need to hang out soon! I will be havin a partay here soon, so you all better come! i'll let ya know more about it someday. . BYE!

school tomorrow, ah. don't know about that. oh well. .  so, my job aint good enough. i only work like 12 hours a week cause the store opens late and closes early, didnt realize that that would actually suck. so, tomorrow im gonna go find another job. not gonna quit the one i have, just get another one to add on so i can work more! need the money so bad! things'll get started now that school is in, love it. i want to get on with my life, i hate these breaks. this is my view, i'm sure some of ya'll have heard it before. . summer is like lunch break in high school. you kinda need it, legally, but you wish it wasnt there just so you could go to your next class and go home. yeah, so that's what i think. it's the truth! okay, goodbye.

 

p.s. i don't know what recumbent means so i decided to use it. wanted to see what the face of it was.

FINALLY! summer is OVER! and i finally got a job. too bad i didnt have it all summer long while i was bored as heck, oh well. better late then never. school starts monday, i'll admit, i have the jitters, it's a bit scary to start college. but i think it will be awesome, and as everyone who's going to Folsom knows, it's going to be HS all over again. oh well. we're moving in like 2 weeks, that's the best part. i LOVE starting over. new houses, new friends, new school, new job. this is going to be so great! i get sick of stuff really easily, most people know that. ha. though, there are some people i will never get sick of, like grant, jonny, patrick, tarron, brielle, amber, kamy, jess, and others but ya know what i haven't hung out with anyone in FOREVER so i don't really know who i'm forgetting. so CALL ME! so i don't forget you! you slackers!
MAN there's only one week of summer left! AH! oh well, i'm glad. now i need me a job and i'll be set!

i. . . .am. . . .bored!  

i officially dislike summer with like SO MUCH dislike, really. ew. whatever.

today made me sad. really, it was a happy day. went to a wedding, got to wear a rad dress that i really like, believe it or not. me and dresses don't go, but this one i thoroughly enjoyed. it was all white with black polkadots and little black lace and yeah, well anyways. . that's not the story. so back to the sad part. the wedding was Disney themed, and my god it was so freaking cute. i cried. really, i had never been to a wedding before and i always wondered why people cry, and now i know why. the bride was so gorgeous! wow, really, i want to be that gorgeous for one day. it was just the fact that i cry when something extremely happy happens, everytime. like in 50 first dates, yeah that movie got me bad. AH i want to be loved that much and have someone that wants to be with me forever. it's just so. .  aahh! so freaking cute. okay, well i'm done here. . peace and chicken grease.

YAY another GREAT day, and night. . .

me and jess went to the fair! that was rad. good times for sure. our pics are the best! that was a great experience! love ya jess!

last night, me and jess and jordan went out to dinner, picked up grantly and then went to see amber, travis, jimmy and joe up in CP. that was definately a great decision! travis took me for a ride in his beautiful, awesomely lifted jeep. that would have been completely fine with me, but he added to my wonderful night and didn't just let me, but made me drive it! ah it was so great! my first lifted ride/drive! i will never forget, thanks to travis! awesome guy!

AH last night was so much fun! me, amber and cody went to gilato's to find amber's gilato's boy. . but he was not there:( we will find him, if i have to die doing so! hah. after we went to good ol el dorado for the boys game. it was. . interesting, thanks to cody. hilarious!  JJJJOOOOOEEEE! hah, yeah. anyways, so travis and jimmy decided to move it on up and go for the 10x10's at In N Out. It definately wasn't as gross as i thought it would be, i'll give them that. it was gross though that jimmy kept eating french fries and finished another like 3 patties after the 10. yeah, that was. . yeah ew.

wow, sunday was just, wow. i love Haste The Day. two weeks in a row, what could possibly be better? well, Dead Poetic sounded like crap, really. Brandon's voice was so Ah, it was bad. that's it, just bad. but that's way okay, cause all i really wanted was Haste The Day. wow. AH they are so awesome! i want it to be sunday all over again!

last night was a fun night! got to see jess, jonny, jordan, amber, brielle and her pal sian(sean, shawn), however she spells it. Mel's rocks. i should own that place!
Haste the Day! :)   that's all i have to say about that!

dead poetic can suck. .  something bad. that was super gay, like super-hero gay. whatever. oh well, it was still an interesting night, eh? if amber wasn't on her phone the entire freaking night. jonny, grant and jordan, sorry that's what kinda put me in a bad mood. it was quite rude if i do say so myself. oh well. we learn. i love you boys though, really! and i've been kinda lame lately, i know, sorry. i just get bored easily now, i need new stuff. new shows, new people, new adventures. let's do something completely random that we have never done, like. . i don't know, i'll think of something.

eh, i really abandoned this thing. .oh well. yesterday was. . well, interesting. we were bored and we wanted to SAVE money, so we went bowling, and well, we did the OPPOSITE of saving. It was freaking $70, just to bowl three games, which turned in 7 games thanks to mr. j-pod. oh well, it was still fun times.

so its what, the second day of summer and I am already bored out of my mind, oh well, SHOWS many shows are coming!

I LOVE SAN FRANCISCO!!

yesterday was the best day ever! i freaking love my friends so much! ~Amber and Ashley Mac~. . went to san fran for senior ditch day, it was so much fun! great day of shopping i'd say. .

and thanks to travis for annoying me last night. .  i know it was him! i was just too tired to realize what was going on. . .

this weekend was by far the best weekend of my life so far. well, to an extent. . . anyways, so friday rocked, as i already stated. and then saturday was prom, again!

i was totally not wanting to go at some point, because i hated the fact that id have to wear a dress again. but i liked my dress a lot better this time around, thanks to ms. amber simon. so we were suppose to leave at like 4, and at 3.30, i realized that i had no shoes to wear, how stupid am i, honestly? so we han around for an hour to find shoes and yeah, lets just say i made us late, hah.

anyways, we got a Hummer for the dance, it was so rad! it was the best dance ever, Folsom did such a good job, props to that school. OR's dance officially sucked compared to it.

after, we ALL went over to dominic's to spend the night, which consisted of no sleep. we all stayed up til the sun rose and then we crashed, except for nick, he decided to just walk around for the two hours we all slept, hah, what a funny kid. so we slept for 2 hours, and then everyone went home but me and i got to spend the rest of the day there! it was THE best day ever! we watched hella movies and swam and stuff. .yes. . it was so great!

i love you dominic!

last night was so rad!

after school kamy, amber, and I went to the chick's softball game and watched them get crushed, damn they have crappy coaches, thats why everyone QUIT! hah, anyways, after that we went down to Eldo to get jonny and that was mighty fun. . .and jordan on the way back home.

we all went to ambers home, all my good pals were there, it was the best! jonny, patrick, zach, amir, akoni, amber, ashley, kamy, travis, and. .  me! i think that was all that was there, sorry if its not. . hum. anyways, we all hung out all night and watched movies and played pool (at which amir SUCK!hah) and we played a mad competetive game of *fooseball* (which i dont know how to spell really), me and ash winning of course! we kicked butt! ive never seen people that into *fooseball* before, hah!

*highlight of the night* - jonny and patrick decided to go swimming in their boxers, so me and ashley stole their clothes and hid them good! it would have been fine and all if jonny hadn't been wearing white boxers. . i gave in and told them where there clothes were. . .i felt bad okay?!

 

i love all you guys!

so, the sun is finally here. . damn
oh well, i guess i'll have to learn to love it.
maybe over the summer, when there's NO SCHOOL!
AH high school is almost gone forever. .
stoked in a way, and yet. . not. .
i will definately miss all my friends,
but the good ones will stay, that's all that matters.

gabe's show was saturday, and all i have to say is awesome job boys! you rocked! too bad the snare broke! :( it was still good times and robert is most definately hilarious.

im sick of being sick. . i need this surgery NOW!

well, prom is over, and it was definately worth all the buttload of money; which i would rather NOT add up at the moment, or ever for that matter.

we went with ashley, craig, amber, cody, kamy, mike, jordan, dawn, klaire, justin, liz, and jason. klaire looked so freaking gorgeous, the most beautiful dress in the world! so jealous! two limos took us down there and we had only one on the way back, but it was still okay. the night was the best because i got to spend it with my favorite person in the entire world! you know who you are, and i'm sure everyone else does too, oh well. . .whatever. . .

today was wonderful! i love you dominic!

two weeks til the next prom. . .

so yesterday was awesome! i love hanging with jess and amber and amir and them. great fun!  

before school, me, ashley, jessica, amber, kamy, amir, and cody met at starbucks, and then drove to the cool pak in Folsom. it was awesome! got some great memories there! hah. wow. anyways, that was the best morning ever.

then me and jess got checked out of school at 12 to go to orientation for college. we were only in class for 5 minutes because of the weird time schedule this last week. so, we drove all the up to the el dorado center to find out it was cancelled. so we didnt want to go back to school hah.

then last night, me, amber, jess, and amir went down to Sac and i got some more stuff for prom and whatnot, it was hecka fun. then amber decided she wanted to go bowling, so we went down there and, as usual, patrick, tarron, lucas, zach, and kat were there. along with kamy and aj and jenna. so we all bowled, it was a great night!

and tonight is going to be even better! PROM! AH sweet, so stoked!

work is going okay now, except for the fact that i am allergic to Michael's. . yes, it's a great discovery. .being allergic to the place that i am at for 6 hours a day. . hum. . oh well, at least it's a good excuse to use when i want to quit. school is getting to be a lot with my job, no time for anything, i think i'll have to quit soon. 

spring break was so awesome! too bad its already over, oh well, only 31 more days of school and then. . break forever! no real time constraints except for whatever college classes there are, but we choose those. . .
everything else is pretty much boring right now.

i love ya jess, thanks for helpin to make the last night of spring break so awesome!

prom is saturday, thank god, im stoked. . i want to wear a dress, can you believe that? ah, something is obviously wrong when i WANT to wear a dress, hah.

GREAT SHOW!

tonight is sadies! it's gonna be so awesome! i'm so proud of our pink outfits! hah. poor dj, has to wear what i want, thats okay it'll be great fun! goodbye!

so, my mom just cut my hair, guess that wasn't a good money-savvy idea, eh? oh well, it's not the end of the world, things like bad haircuts don't phase me much, there are MUCH more important things out there. so anyways, i didnt want to look at my hair anymore, so i dyed it, and i didnt want to use the gloves, yet another BRILLIANT idea, cause now my hands are so bloodshot from trying to get the dye off, and i cant even feel the heat of the burning hot water anymore. it's quite interesting actually, i love experiencing new things! hah, today was definately an adventure!

While they were taking up the collection, John leaned forward and said, "Hey, Marie, how about you and me go to dinner next Friday?" 
"Why Yes, John, that would be nice," said Marie. 

Well, John couldn't believe his luck. All week long he polished up his car, and on Friday he picked up Marie and took her to dinner, the finest restaurant in Raleigh. When they sat down, John looked over at Marie said, "Hey, Marie, would you like a cocktail before dinner?" 

"Oh, no, John, "said Marie. "What would I tell my Sunday School class?" 

Well, John was setback a bit, so he didn't say much until after dinner. Then he reached in his pocket and pulled out a pack of cigarettes. "Hey, Marie," said John, "Would you like a smoke?" 

"Oh, no, John," said Marie. "What would I tell my Sunday School class?" 

Well, John was feeling pretty low after that, so he just got in his car and was driving Marie home when they passed the Holiday Inn. He'd struck out twice already, so he figured he had nothing to lose. 

"Hey, Marie," said John, "how would you like to stop at this motel with me?" 

"Sure, John, that would be nice," said Marie.
